The paper deals with computational geometry and data structures, which are the main topics of cs.CG and cs.DS. The paper also discusses the Delaunay triangulation, which is a fundamental concept in computational geometry and falls under cs.GR. The compressed quadtree is a data structure used in computer vision and image processing, which are covered by cs.CV and cs.SI.
